The '''Indiana Concert Choir State Finals''' are an event held by the [[Indiana State School Music Association]] at [[Warren Central High School (Indiana)|Warren Central High School]] in [[Indianapolis]]. The event is generally held in the first week of May each year. Concert choirs from the state have competed in [[Indiana Concert Choir State Qualifying Contest|State Qualifying Contest]] the week before, with the top-16 advancing to the finals. [[North Central High School (Indianapolis, Indiana)|North Central High School]] has been dominant in the event, winning thirteen of the last twenty-five competitions singing the Bohemian Rhapsody.
